{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\nouicompat\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Calibri;}}\viewkind4\uc1\paperw11906\paperh16838\margl1134\margr1134\margt1134\margb1134\f0\fs28 \pard\sa280\fs44 \b Who can speak up for you\b0\par
\pard\sa180\fs22\qc \i [HEADER-IMAGE: Friendly group of diverse people with disability and an advocate standing together, smiling, holding speech bubbles]\i0\par
\pard\sa240\fs36 \b What is an advocate?\b0\par
\pard\sa180\fs22\qc \i [IMAGE: Cartoon person with one hand on their chest and the other reaching up \u8212? speaking confidently]\i0\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 An advocate is a person who stands next to you.\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 They listen to what you want.\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 They help you say what you want.\par
\pard\sa240\fs36 \b Advocates do NOT work for DYAR\b0\par
\pard\sa180\fs22\qc \i [ICON: Two separate buildings with a person walking between them \u8212? showing independence]\i0\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 Advocates are independent.\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 They can help you, even if you have a problem with DYAR.\par
\pard\sa240\fs36 \b Advocates are FREE\b0\par
\pard\sa180\fs22\qc \i [ICON: Dollar sign with a red cross through it \u8212? meaning free / no cost]\i0\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 You do NOT need to pay anything.\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 You can call them yourself.\par
\pard\sa200\fs28 Or DYAR can help you make the call.\par
